   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">The Meeting Scheduler feature enables you to create Zoom meetings in <ph conref="../../../Warehouse/Product_Name_Warehouse.dita#reference-9043/product_name"
             class="- topic/ph "/>. <ph product="Include_in_Emp_PG" class="- topic/ph ">The Zoom authorization is performed as part of project collaboration. For more details refer to <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Training Manual - Mind Build (Part 03)</i>
         </ph>
         <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content" class="- topic/ph ">For information in Meeting Scheduler, refer to<xref href="../../Project_Management/Collaboration/Meeting_Scheduler/MeetSch.dita"
                  class="- topic/xref ">Meeting Scheduler</xref>.</ph>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the module menu, click<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Administration</uicontrol>. </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "> The<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ADMINISTRATION</uicontrol> page is displayed. </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the navigation pane, expand<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Functional Configurations</uicontrol>, and thenclick<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Meeting Settings</uicontrol>. </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">MEETING SETTINGS</uicontrol>page is displayed. </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">By default, the<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Enable Zoom Meeting Scheduler</uicontrol>check box is selected thatindicates the Meeting Scheduler feature is enabled in the application.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">To turn off theMeeting Scheduler feature, clear the check box. </info>
         </step>
